# RotHunter path-ignore file.
#
# Standard `.gitignore` syntax — patterns here are layered on TOP of
# `.gitignore` to exclude paths from rothunter scans without touching
# what git sees. Use this for files that ARE checked into git but
# rothunter shouldn't analyse (fixtures, generated SDKs, vendored
# third-party copies, large data dumps).
#
# To suppress an INDIVIDUAL FINDING by fingerprint (not a path),
# write to `.rothunter/snoozed-fingerprints.txt` instead.
#
# Examples:
#   # Detector own-test fixtures — flagged-by-design code samples.
#   src/__fixtures__/
#
#   # Vendored SDK clients
#   packages/*/vendor/
#
#   # Large generated CSV fixtures
#   data/large/*.csv

# Detector own-test fixtures — these files exist to TRIGGER detectors
# (intentional duplicates / races / mutations) so rothunter shouldn't
# treat its own bait as a real finding.
src/__fixtures__/
